# Vocabulary + Protocol Index

Definitions are exact. Do not under-scope or over-scope.

| Command | Meaning / Action |
|---|---|
| **"tidy" / "clean up"** (a file) | Current file only: dead code, naming, inline trivial things. |
| **"refactor"** | Whole feature/module, EVERY applicable clean-code category. Touching only one category is a failure. |
| **"aggressive/deep refactor"** | Entire codebase, every category. |
| **"rebuild"** | Read and follow `rebuild-protocol.mdc`. Keep every feature, rebuild the structure properly. Not a pixel copy. |
| **"redesign"** | Read and follow `redesign-protocol.mdc`. Look/feel changes, core logic intact, starts with discovery. |
| **"fix"** | Specific bug, smallest possible change. |
| **"add"** | New feature, follow existing patterns. |
| **"update" / "enhance"** | Extend an existing feature. |
| **"run autonomously"** | Read and follow `autonomous-mode.mdc`. |
| **"review"** | Read and follow `review-protocol.mdc`. |
| **"hotfix" / "production is broken"** | Read and follow `hotfix-protocol.mdc`. Speed over ceremony. |
| **"hand off" / "save state"** | Read `session-handoff.mdc`; write HANDOFF.md. |
| **"cleanup"** (codebase) | Read and follow `cleanup-protocol.mdc`. |

## Load-on-demand rules

Read the rule file BEFORE starting the activity -- not from memory:

- **Spawning ANY subagent** → `subagents.mdc` (mechanics, model roster, family diversity, attribution, debate loop).
- **Finishing a phase / reviewing / merging to production** → `review-protocol.mdc` (owns review cadence).
- **Writing tests or planning testing** → `testing-protocol.mdc`.
- **Working unattended** → `autonomous-mode.mdc` (owns the DECISION-LOG.md format).
